<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key F (1 flat). 3/4 waltz feel. LH open voicing on each beat.
- Two strophe repetitions (bars 1-8, 9-16) then middle section (17-24).
- Opening: Half-note chords in LH, light RH thirds. Sparse and graceful.
- Middle section: Gm color (bars 17,19,22,23) adding modal darkness before final cadence.
- Bar 21: Climax on C5 with full F tonic voicing.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH stays 2 notes throughout (C5-E5, F4-A4 thirds) — light soprano register
- LH bass descends F-C-F-Bb stepwise, contrary motion with ascending melody
- Common tone C held between F, C, and Gm chords in LH

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-8: Serene 3/4, light 2-note RH over open LH
- Bars 9-16: Same, slightly more motion
- Bars 17-24: Gm color → climax bar 21 → resolution bar 24
-->
